<TITLE> Mamun's bail in tax-dodge case halted </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 26 (bdnews24.com)--The Appellate Division on Monday briefly halted the bail granted by the High Court to controversial businessman Giasuddin Al Mamun in a tax evasion case, a lawyer said. His bail order has been frozen up to Thursday to hear the government's petition at the regular bench of the Appellate Division, barrister Rafiq-Ul Haque, his lawyer, told bdnews24.com after the hearing. The Appellate Division chamber judge, Justice Mohammad Mozammel Hossain, gave the order upon an appeal filed by the government. Mamun secured a six-month interim bail from the High Court on Oct 20. Nazrul Islam Talukder, a deputy attorney general, represented the state at the Monday's hearing. The National Board of Revenue filed the tax-dodge case with Dhaka Metropolitan sessions and special judge's court on Aug 26. The case charged him with evading Tk 13 crore in taxes. b
